  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6596.24 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-27B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+27B), dealers are in a critical hedging zone where they're likely buying this dip given the negative gamma dominance below current levels. The BREAKOUT regime with -30B total GEX means any directional move will be amplified by dealer flow - if we break below 6590, expect accelerated selling as dealers short more into weakness, while a push above 6605 should trigger dealer selling that could cap the rally. Key battle zone is 6590-6605 with massive gamma walls creating a narrow amplification corridor that should produce violent intraday swings.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect explosive moves in either direction within the tight 6590-6605 range, then trending action on any breakout.",
